title.narrative: New Element

description.narrative: There has been impressive progress in the implementation of the WASH program activities and achievement of the planned deliverables. In 2021, UNICEF combined COVID-19 response, floods response and routine WASH program interventions and was able to upgrade water, sanitation and hygiene (WASH) services of 25 Community Health Centers (CHCs) in 6 municipalities. Improvement of WASH in these CHCs translated to approximately 25,000 people accessing WASH services at their CHCs, thus directly reducing the risk of infection for health staff and people seeking services in communities while indirectly improving the quality of corresponding health services by those CHCs. | Status:Met | As-of Date:31/12/2021
